{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871028422,"sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","part":{"id":"prt_d7a27c9f4001K1XMAavSyfJJed","messageID":"msg_d7a2778f7001xyIEXGBK0eMnzb","sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md","content":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nThis plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n\n## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n- [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n- [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n- [ ] Document error codes and status states\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n\n- [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n- [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n- [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n- [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n\n## Phase 3: Output Handling\n\n- [ ] Design output capture mechanism\n- [ ] Implement stdout/stderr collection\n- [ ] Add output streaming support (buffer-based)\n- [ ] Handle large output scenarios\n\n## Phase 4: Error Handling and Status\n\n- [ ] Implement execution status lifecycle\n- [ ] Add timeout and cancellation support\n- [ ] Design error translation layer\n- [ ] Add execution result metadata\n\n## Phase 5: Testing\n\n- [ ] Write unit tests for execution logic\n- [ ] Create mock sandbox for testing\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n- [ ] Performance and resource limit tests\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- AR-009: Sandbox orchestration system (for integration)\n- AR-012: Session storage interface (for status persistence)\n\n## Estimated Timeline\n\n- Phase 1: 1 day\n- Phase 2: 1.5 days\n- Phase 3: 1 day\n- Phase 4: 0.5 day\n- Phase 5: 1 day\n\nTotal: 4-5 days\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md","time":{"start":1775871028386,"end":1775871028420}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871028424,"sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","part":{"id":"prt_d7a27f73b001z8KFMGFGl1rHIj","messageID":"msg_d7a2778f7001xyIEXGBK0eMnzb","sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","content":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Interfaces\n\n#### CommandExecutor\n\nThe primary interface for executing commands through PicoD.\n\n```go\ntype CommandExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n    ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n    GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n    Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n    StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionRequest\n\nConfiguration for a command execution.\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionRequest struct {\n    Command     string\n    Args        []string\n    WorkingDir  string\n    Environment map[string]string\n    Timeout     time.Duration\n    ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n    SessionID   string\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionResult\n\nResult of a command execution.\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionResult struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    Status     ExecutionStatus\n    ExitCode   int\n    Stdout     []byte\n    Stderr     []byte\n    StartedAt  time.Time\n    FinishedAt time.Time\n    Error      *ExecutionError\n}\n```\n\n## Data Flow\n\n### Synchronous Execution\n\n```\n1. Client calls Execute()\n2. PicoD validates request and resource limits\n3. Sandbox environment is prepared\n4. Command is executed with monitoring\n5. Output is captured\n6. Result is returned to client\n```\n\n### Asynchronous Execution\n\n```\n1. Client calls ExecuteAsync()\n2. Execution is queued with initial status \"pending\"\n3. Background worker picks up execution\n4. Status updates to \"running\"\n5. Output is streamed to buffer\n6. On completion, status updates to \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n7. Client polls GetStatus() or receives callback\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n- `ErrInvalidRequest`: Malformed execution request\n- `ErrResourceExceeded`: Resource limits exceeded\n- `ErrTimeout`: Execution exceeded timeout\n- `ErrSandboxUnavailable`: Sandbox environment not available\n- `ErrExecutionFailed`: Command returned non-zero exit code\n- `ErrCancelled`: Execution was cancelled\n\n### Status States\n\n```\npending → running → completed\n              ↓\n            failed\n              ↓\n           cancelled\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- Commands run in isolated sandbox environment\n- Resource limits enforced at sandbox level\n- No direct shell access\n- Environment variable filtering\n- Working directory restrictions\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n- Connection pooling to sandbox service\n- Output buffering with size limits\n- Concurrent execution limits\n- Timeout enforcement at multiple levels\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Maximum output size limits?\n2. Real-time streaming protocol?\n3. Multi-tenancy isolation model?\n4. Execution queue prioritization?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775871028391,"end":1775871028423}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871028427,"sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2850ed001053FSRKf2CnxoC","messageID":"msg_d7a2778f7001xyIEXGBK0eMnzb","sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Delta Specification\n\n## Changes to Existing Code\n\n### New Files\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── executor.go       # Core CommandExecutor implementation\n├── executor_test.go  # Unit tests\n├── types.go          # Request/response types\n├── status.go         # Execution status management\n├── output.go         # Output capture and streaming\n└── errors.go         # Error definitions\n```\n\n### Interfaces Added\n\n```go\n// pkg/picod/types.go\n\ntype ExecutionID string\n\ntype ExecutionRequest struct {\n    Command        string\n    Args           []string\n    WorkingDir     string\n    Environment    map[string]string\n    Timeout        time.Duration\n    ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n    SessionID      string\n}\n\ntype ExecutionResult struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    Status     ExecutionStatus\n    ExitCode   int\n    Stdout     []byte\n    Stderr     []byte\n    StartedAt  time.Time\n    FinishedAt time.Time\n    Error      *ExecutionError\n}\n\ntype ExecutionStatus struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    State      ExecutionState\n    StartedAt  *time.Time\n    FinishedAt *time.Time\n    ExitCode   *int\n}\n\ntype ExecutionState string\n\nconst (\n    StatePending    ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n    StateRunning    ExecutionState = \"running\"\n    StateCompleted  ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n    StateFailed     ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n    StateCancelled  ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype ResourceConstraints struct {\n    MaxMemory   int64         // bytes\n    MaxCPU      float64       // percentage\n    MaxIOBytes  int64         // bytes per second\n    MaxFiles    int\n}\n\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    Code    string\n    Message string\n    Details map[string]interface{}\n}\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/sandbox` (AR-009): Sandbox interface for command execution\n- `pkg/store` (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014): For execution status persistence\n\n### Configuration\n\nNew configuration options:\n\n```yaml\npicod:\n  default_timeout: 30s\n  max_concurrent_executions: 100\n  max_output_size: 10MB\n  output_buffer_size: 4KB\n```\n\n## API Surface\n\n### Public API\n\n```go\n// NewCommandExecutor creates a new PicoD command executor\nfunc NewCommandExecutor(sandbox SandboxClient, store StatusStore, opts ExecutorOptions) (*CommandExecutor, error)\n\n// Execute runs a command synchronously\nfunc (e *CommandExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n\n// ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously\nfunc (e *CommandExecutor) ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n\n// GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution\nfunc (e *CommandExecutor) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n\n// Cancel stops a running execution\nfunc (e *CommandExecutor) Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n\n// StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output\nfunc (e *CommandExecutor) StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n```\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n- Commands are now executed through PicoD API instead of direct sandbox calls\n- Resource limits are enforced at the API layer\n- All executions are tracked with persistent status\n- Output is captured and can be streamed\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- Existing direct sandbox usage should migrate to PicoD API\n- No breaking changes to sandbox interface\n- PicoD API is additive layer on top of existing components\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871028396,"end":1775871028425}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871028428,"sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","part":{"id":"prt_d7a28ae9f001kN1ck3AtrSMYpm","messageID":"msg_d7a2778f7001xyIEXGBK0eMnzb","sessionID":"ses_285d8d820ffeeN7duQVkTRpVaN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tests.md","content":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Test Specification\n\n## Test Categories\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### executor_test.go\n\n```go\n// TestExecute_Success - Basic successful execution\n// TestExecute_Timeout - Execution timeout handling\n// TestExecute_ResourceLimit - Resource limit enforcement\n// TestExecute_InvalidCommand - Invalid command handling\n// TestExecute_SandboxError - Sandbox failure handling\n\n// TestExecuteAsync_Success - Basic async execution\n// TestExecuteAsync_QueueFull - Queue capacity handling\n// TestExecuteAsync_Cancellation - Async execution cancellation\n\n// TestGetStatus_Pending - Status retrieval for pending\n// TestGetStatus_Running - Status retrieval for running\n// TestGetStatus_Completed - Status retrieval for completed\n// TestGetStatus_NotFound - Non-existent execution\n\n// TestCancel_Running - Cancel running execution\n// TestCancel_Completed - Cancel already completed\n// TestCancel_NotFound - Cancel non-existent\n\n// TestStreamOutput_RealTime - Output streaming\n// TestStreamOutput_LargeOutput - Large output handling\n// TestStreamOutput_Closed - Stream closure handling\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### executor_integration_test.go\n\n```go\n// TestIntegration_EndToEnd - Full execution flow\n// TestIntegration_ConcurrentExecutions - Multiple parallel executions\n// TestIntegration_ResourceContention - Resource limit scenarios\n// TestIntegration_StatusPersistence - Status storage/retrieval\n// TestIntegration_CancellationRace - Race condition handling\n```\n\n### Mock Implementations\n\n```go\n// MockSandboxClient - Mock sandbox for testing\n// MockStatusStore - Mock status storage\n// MockResourceLimiter - Mock resource limiting\n```\n\n## Test Data\n\n### Sample Commands\n\n```go\nvar testCommands = []struct {\n    name    string\n    command string\n    args    []string\n    wantErr bool\n}{\n    {\"echo\", \"echo\", []string{\"hello\"}, false},\n    {\"exit_0\", \"true\", nil, false},\n    {\"exit_1\", \"false\", nil, true},\n    {\"sleep\", \"sleep\", []string{\"0.1\"}, false},\n    {\"invalid\", \"__invalid_command__\", nil, true},\n}\n```\n\n### Resource Limit Test Cases\n\n```go\nvar resourceTests = []struct {\n    name      string\n    memory    int64\n    cpu       float64\n    wantLimit bool\n}{\n    {\"within_limits\", 1024 * 1024 * 100, 50.0, false},\n    {\"exceed_memory\", 1024 * 1024 * 1024, 50.0, true},\n    {\"exceed_cpu\", 1024 * 1024 * 100, 150.0, true},\n}\n```\n\n## Coverage Targets\n\n- Line coverage: >= 85%\n- Branch coverage: >= 80%\n- Critical paths: 100%\n\n## Test Environment\n\n- Go 1.21+\n- Mock sandbox implementation\n- In-memory status store for unit tests\n- Docker-based sandbox for integration tests\n\n## Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests only\ngo test ./pkg/picod/... -short\n\n# All tests including integration\ngo test ./pkg/picod/...\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tests.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tests.md","time":{"start":1775871028399,"end":1775871028427}}}}
